---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Pre Approved Personal Loan - Instant Approval | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="#">Loans</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Pre Approved Personal Loan</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Pre Approved Personal Loan</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Get a pre-approved personal loan with instant approval and zero documentation for existing bank customers. Enjoy preferential interest rates starting at 9.49% p.a. with disbursal in under 30 minutes directly to your bank account.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-indian-rupee-sign"></i>
          <span>Loan Amount: ₹50K - ₹50L</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-days"></i>
          <span>Tenure: 1-5 Years</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Interest: 9.49% onwards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What is a Pre Approved Personal Loan?</h2>
          <p>A pre-approved personal loan is a loan offer extended by your bank or NBFC based on your existing relationship, transaction history, salary credits, and credit profile. Unlike regular personal loans, pre-approved offers require minimal or zero documentation since the lender has already assessed your creditworthiness. These offers typically come with lower interest rates, higher loan amounts, and instant disbursal — often within 30 minutes of acceptance.</p>
          <p>At TrueCred Loan Expert, we help you discover pre-approved loan offers from your existing banks and new lenders. Our platform aggregates pre-qualified offers from over 60 banks and NBFCs, allowing you to compare and choose the best deal. If you are a salaried professional with a salary account at a major bank, chances are high that you already have a pre-approved offer waiting — check now and save thousands on interest.</p>

          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">9.49%</span>
              <span class="info-label">Interest Rate (p.a.)</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">₹50 Lakh</span>
              <span class="info-label">Max Loan Amount</span>
            </div>
            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-value">30 Min</span>
              <span class="info-label">Disbursal Time</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Pre Approved Personal Loan Rates — April 2026</h3>
          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Bank / NBFC</th>
                <th>Interest Rate (p.a.)</th>
                <th>Processing Fee</th>
                <th>Max Tenure</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>HDFC Bank</td>
                <td>9.49% onwards</td>
                <td>Nil</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>SBI</td>
                <td>9.75% onwards</td>
                <td>Nil</td>
                <td>6 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>ICICI Bank</td>
                <td>9.99% onwards</td>
                <td>Up to 1.00%</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Kotak Mahindra Bank</td>
                <td>10.25% onwards</td>
                <td>Nil</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Axis Bank</td>
                <td>9.85% onwards</td>
                <td>Nil</td>
                <td>5 Years</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h3>Eligibility Criteria</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Existing customer of the bank with active savings/salary account</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Minimum salary credit of ₹25,000 per month for at least 6 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> CIBIL score of 720 or above (may vary by lender)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Age between 23 and 58 years at the time of loan maturity</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> No outstanding defaults or delinquencies in the last 12 months</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Employed with a reputed organization listed in the bank's approved employer list</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Avail Your Pre Approved Loan</h3>
          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Check Your Offer</h4>
              <p>Log in to your net banking or mobile banking app to check if you have a pre-approved personal loan offer from your bank.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Review Terms</h4>
              <p>Compare the interest rate, processing fee, loan amount, and EMI offered. Use our EMI calculator to plan repayment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Accept & Verify</h4>
              <p>Accept the offer with a single click. Complete e-KYC verification via Aadhaar OTP — no physical documents needed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Instant Disbursal</h4>
              <p>The approved loan amount is credited to your salary account within 30 minutes of acceptance. Start using funds immediately.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Documents Required</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> No physical documents required for most pre-approved offers</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Aadhaar-based e-KYC for identity and address verification</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> PAN Card for income tax verification (auto-fetched in most cases)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Digital consent for credit bureau check</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Bank statement not required — lender uses existing account data</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-circle-check"></i> Salary slips not required — bank verifies from salary credits</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i> Check Pre Approved Offer</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Loan Amount</option>
                  <option value="100000">₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="200000">₹2,00,000</option>
                  <option value="300000">₹3,00,000</option>
                  <option value="500000">₹5,00,000</option>
                  <option value="1000000">₹10,00,000</option>
                  <option value="2000000">₹20,00,000</option>
                  <option value="3000000">₹30,00,000</option>
                  <option value="4000000">₹40,00,000</option>
                  <option value="5000000">₹50,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="City" required>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
            </form>
          </div>

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <div class="sidebar-links">
              <a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Business Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Home Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/loan-against-property"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Loan Against Property</a>
              <a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Gold Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/education-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Education Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/car-loan"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Car Loan</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Cards</a>
              <a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Credit Score</a>
              <a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> EMI Calculator</a>
              <a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i> Insurance</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">Got Questions?</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about pre-approved personal loans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            How do I know if I have a pre-approved personal loan offer?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Most banks notify eligible customers via SMS, email, net banking pop-ups, or mobile banking notifications. You can also check by logging into your bank's internet banking portal or mobile app under the loans section. On TrueCred, simply enter your details and we'll show you all available pre-approved offers across multiple banks.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Is a pre-approved loan different from a pre-qualified loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Yes. A pre-approved loan is a firm offer where the bank has already verified your eligibility and credit profile — acceptance leads to guaranteed disbursal. A pre-qualified loan is a softer indication based on basic criteria, and final approval may still require additional verification and documentation.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Can I negotiate the interest rate on a pre-approved loan?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Pre-approved offers already come at preferential rates lower than standard personal loans. While there is limited room for negotiation, you can compare offers from multiple banks on TrueCred and choose the lowest rate. Having a CIBIL score above 800 or a long banking relationship may unlock even better rates.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            What happens if I decline a pre-approved offer?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Declining a pre-approved offer does not affect your credit score or banking relationship. The offer may expire after the validity period (usually 30-60 days), but banks often extend new offers periodically based on your continued eligibility. You can always check for updated offers on TrueCred.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            Is there any processing fee for pre-approved personal loans?
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              Many banks waive the processing fee entirely for pre-approved personal loans as an incentive. Some lenders may charge a nominal fee of up to 1% of the loan amount. Always compare the total cost including processing fee, prepayment charges, and interest rate before accepting an offer.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-content" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-cta">
        <div>
          <h3>Check Your Pre Approved Loan Offer Now</h3>
          <p>Discover instant loan offers from your bank with rates as low as 9.49% p.a. and zero documentation.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline" style="color:#fff;border:2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5);padding:14px 32px;font-size:0.95rem;">
          Apply Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
